        "title": "feat(slides): add native table creation",
        "body": "## Summary\n- add `gog slides table create` for native Slides tables with `--rows`, `--cols`, `--x`, `--y`, `--width`, `--height`, and `--unit`\n- extend `gog slides insert-text` with optional `--row` and `--col` table-cell targeting while preserving existing shape/object text behavior\n- add focused request-construction and validation tests, then regenerate generated command docs\n\nFixes https://github.com/openclaw/gogcli/issues/824\n\n## Release note\nAdds a first native Google Slides table surface: create tables and write text into individual table cells. Row/column insert/delete, merge/unmerge, borders, styling, and dimension operations remain future scope.\n\n## Credit\nThanks @sebsnyk for the report and requested command shape in #824.\n\n## Validation\n- `make fmt`\n- `go test ./internal/cmd -run 'TestSlides(Table|InsertText)'`\n- `make docs-commands`\n- `make ci`\n",
